<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{2}{y}=-{22}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{8}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{2}{y}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{22}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{22}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{-{22}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}\right)}+{8}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{8}}}}\cdot{\left(-{22}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+{8}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11}-{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}+{8}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{y}+{\left({8}\right)}{y}={24}--{11}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{y}+{\left({8}\right)}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{1}+{\left({8}\right)}\right)}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{y}={35}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{35}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{2}{\left({5}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{\left({10}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{22}-{\left({10}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{32}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{32}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

